      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "d730750a6311cae8a4427824867410faccc6698f",
            "subject": "LU-5651: ptlrpc: fix import state during replay"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-09-23 13:00:27.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-11-04 18:06:00.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5545 ptlrpc: false alarm in AT network latency measuring",
        "message": "LU-5545 ptlrpc: false alarm in AT network latency measuring\n\nIf early reply of client RPC is lost and client RPC is expired and\nresent, server will drop the resent RPC because it's already in\nprocessing, server may also send reply or early reply to client,\nwhich can still match reply buffer of the original request.\nIn this case, client is measuring time from resent time, but server\nis reporting service time of original RPC, which is longer than\nthe time measured by client.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I772fb054480a3212e28dc018a6f592f3da7a87b5\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/12018\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Li Wei <wei.g.li@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Johann Lombardi <johann.lombardi@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
